'''Alex Boone''' (born May 4, 1987 in {{city-state|Lakewood|Ohio}}) is an [[offensive tackle]] for the [[San Francisco 49ers]]. He played college football for the [[Ohio State Buckeyes football|Ohio State Buckeyes]]. He was regarded as a top prospect at his position in the [[2009 NFL Draft]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.draftcountdown.com/rankings/ot.php|title=www.draftcountdown.com/rankings/ot.php<!--INSERT TITLE-->}}</ref> but concerns about his alcohol use, which has included up to thirty to forty beers a day and two alcohol-related arrests, have impacted his draft positioning.<ref>[http://www.ohio.com/sports/osu/39878257.html OSU's Boone Trying to Save Career] Ohio.com, February 19, 2009</ref>

He was convicted of [[driving under the influence]] in 2006<ref>[http://www.nytimes.com/2009/02/20/sports/football/20combine.html?ref=ncaafootball Ohio State Tackle Gets NFL's Attentio in the Wrong Way] NY Times, February 20, 2009</ref> and was arrested on February 1, 2009 after allegedly jumping on car hoods, yanking on a tow truck cable and trying to break a window; police reports indicate that they were forced to [[taser]] Boone to subdue him.<ref>[http://www.nytimes.com/aponline/2009/02/02/sports/AP-FBC-Ohio-St-Boone-Arrested.html Ohio State OL Boone Arrested in California] NY Times, February 2, 2009</ref>

He played [[high school football]] at [[St. Edward High School (Lakewood, Ohio)|St. Edward High School]] in Lakewood. After being signed by the San Francisco 49ers as an Unrestricted Free Agent following the 2009 NFL Draft, he was released on the final day of roster cuts.

